content: This week Sean Casten and his allies on the political left took to social media to exploit the Coronavirus pandemic for political gain. On Saturday, Sean Casten tweeted out, “To bet on Trump is to bet against the American people.” #IL06 #twill https://t.co/w7xi36jvru

Indivisible DuPage, an organization that openly supports Casten & w/whom he worked closely to get elected -  followed up with a Facebook graphic that strings together a series of charges to accuse Republicans of 'killing Americans.' #IL06 #twill https://t.co/7gA1Ps03cH

“In one weekend, Sean Casten equated those who voted for President Trump with traitors, and Indivisible DuPage called hundreds of thousands of good people in the 6th District killers. Killers. #IL06 #twill

This is the most extreme and divisive rhetoric at a time when all Americans are fearful about their futures and their well-being,” said Jeanne Ives, a candidate for Congress in IL-06. “I am offended, as a veteran, a military mom, and a citizen. We all should be offended. #IL06

Everyone is concerned about the health and the economic cost of this crisis. Regardless of party or political beliefs, our leaders should be working together to ensure we get past this pandemic and get American workers back on the job - not stoking anger, fear and division. #IL06

“Where is the media on this? Why haven’t they pushed back on the exploitation of the pandemic by Democrats in the same rigorous way they cover Republicans? If it matters what Trump says intemperately, then it matters what Casten says ignorantly. #IL06 #twill
"In a crisis, character matters most. And Sean Casten and Indivisible DuPage are certainly showing their true character." #IL06 #twill

While Sean Casten focuses on political attacks, Jeanne Ives focused on the nation’s problem-solving spirit. 

This morning, she released a new ad, illustrating her campaign theme: Americans have the ingenuity, compassion & grit to solve our toughest challenges. #Il06   #twill https://t.co/NM5FhVRI0o

In a new video from a recent Indivisible DuPage interview video, Sean Casten says, “I believe that the president is prioritizing keeping the number of [coronavirus] cases low over saving lives… and I can’t prove that.” 

https://t.co/B4EfF5JiJ6

That’s just a weird thing to say. Of course, keeping the number of cases low is a priority. It’s a priority for everyone - from Donald Trump to Lori Lightfoot - because slowing down the number of cases means slowing down the number of deaths.

https://t.co/B4EfF5JiJ6

The fact that Casten can’t understand that - or is trying to spin it into a bad thing - is just strange. This district needs a rep who speaks plainly about workable solutions to our most pressing problems, not a guy who mumbles in hushed tones about half-baked conspiracies.”
